1
00:00:00,416 --> 00:00:03,000
Younes Basil
Muhammad, from Mosul

2
00:00:03,041 --> 00:00:04,541
I am 24 years old

3
00:00:05,708 --> 00:00:07,750
I am not studying or
working at the moment

4
00:00:10,208 --> 00:00:12,375
Interviewer: Are you married?
Witness: No, I’m not married

5
00:00:14,375 --> 00:00:17,791
Tell me about your first
detention experience

6
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:19,875
Where were you arrested,
and where did they take you?

7
00:00:19,875 --> 00:00:22,916
How long did you stay in the place where you
were detained, and what happened to you there?

8
00:00:24,416 --> 00:00:25,708
They took me from the house

9
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:28,333
To the Dawasa Center

10
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:30,000
I stayed with them there

11
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,666
I stayed with them there

12
00:00:33,125 --> 00:00:36,875
And I was tortured, and so on

13
00:00:37,750 --> 00:00:41,166
Then I was transferred to the
<i>Qaimaqam</i> Prison

14
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:43,250
I stayed there for a week

15
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:45,875
Then they transferred
me back here

16
00:00:45,916 --> 00:00:48,916
Two days after I was transferred
there, the place was bombed

17
00:00:49,166 --> 00:00:50,500
A plane bombed it

18
00:00:51,625 --> 00:00:55,166
I came and spent one
month and twenty days here

19
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:56,125
Interviewer: Okay

20
00:00:56,875 --> 00:01:01,250
When they took you there,
what day was it and at what time?

21
00:01:01,291 --> 00:01:04,166
And what was the date when they
came and took you from the house?

22
00:01:04,708 --> 00:01:06,791
What conversation
took place between you?

23
00:01:07,583 --> 00:01:09,000
They took me before Ramadan

24
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,208
They said, We just
need you for a question

25
00:01:13,541 --> 00:01:16,333
We only want to ask you something,
then we’ll return you home

26
00:01:18,083 --> 00:01:21,166
When we reached the
center, they didn’t let me leave

27
00:01:21,208 --> 00:01:24,083
And they told my father, Go, we’ll
keep your son and we won’t let him out

28
00:01:25,416 --> 00:01:26,625
So I stayed two days

29
00:01:27,791 --> 00:01:29,833
Ramadan was near

30
00:01:30,416 --> 00:01:31,583
Ramadan was approaching

31
00:01:34,083 --> 00:01:35,916
I spent the whole
month of Ramadan here

32
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:38,625
On <i>Laylat al-Qadr</i>,
they cut off my hand

33
00:01:38,666 --> 00:01:40,375
They took me out of here
and amputated my hand
